What you need to know:

“This is what I’ve advocated for a long time. It’s a welcome move as the committee has mature people and we look forward to a positive revival of cricket because the game is bigger than anyone,” said Karim who was called out of retirement to lead Kenya to the 2003 Cricket World Cup semis in South Africa.Amina said the Normalisation Committee is expected to hold its first meeting on March 22 and co-ordinate the drafting of a new federation constitution in compliance with the Sports Act (2013).